  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7103 sitting just above the 7100 GEX wall (+5.1B) and well above the flip at 7047, dealers are in PIN regime and likely selling into this move as they hedge their long gamma positions. The massive positive gamma walls at 7100/7150/7200 create a strong gravitational pull that should cap upside momentum, with dealers becoming increasingly aggressive sellers as we approach the 7200 max gamma level (+7.8B). Key levels to watch: support at 7100 where dealers flip from selling to buying, and resistance building toward 7150-7200 where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect the market to get pulled back toward 7100 with limited upside past 7150.",
